click_me — Web Challenge

Challenge Description

The challenge presents a webpage containing a single button labeled “Click Me”.
Clicking the button redirects the user to another page with the same layout but a different URL path consisting of a 32-character hexadecimal string.

Example path:

/a04adb225ce0e3f2732efa132137ee0b

Each page contains exactly one link to the next hash, forming a long redirection chain.

The objective is to reach the end of the chain and retrieve the flag.

Initial Analysis

No input fields, parameters, or authentication

No visible client-side logic or JavaScript manipulation

No traditional vulnerabilities (SQLi, XSS, SSTI, LFI, etc.)

Each page returns static HTML with a single anchor tag:

<a href="/<32_hex>">Click Me</a>

The chain length is intentionally large (hundreds to thousands of steps), making manual traversal impractical.

This confirms the challenge is automation-based, not vulnerability-based.

Intended Solution

The intended approach is to automate HTTP requests, recursively following each hash until the flag is discovered.

Key requirements:

Extract the next hash from each response

Track visited hashes to avoid loops

Detect the flag in page content or terminal responses (e.g., 404)

Exploitation Strategy

Open the initial page and extract the first hash

Send an HTTP GET request to /hash

Parse the response for:

The next hash (href="/[0-9a-f]{32}")

A flag pattern (flag{} or Flag{})

Repeat until the flag is found or the chain ends

Implementation

Asynchronous Traversal 

Asynchronous requests significantly reduce execution time and prevent instance expiration.

import aiohttp
import asyncio
import re

async def traverse(start_hash, base_url):
    visited = set()
    current = start_hash
    step = 0

    async with aiohttp.ClientSession() as session:
        while current not in visited:
            visited.add(current)
            step += 1
            url = f"{base_url}/{current}"
            print(f"[{step}] {url}")

            async with session.get(url, timeout=5) as resp:
                text = await resp.text()

                flag = re.search(r'(?:flag|Flag)\{[^}]+\}', text, re.I)
                if flag:
                    print("\n[+] FLAG FOUND")
                    print(flag.group(0))
                    return

                nxt = re.search(r'href="/([0-9a-f]{32})"', text)
                if not nxt:
                    print("[!] Chain terminated")
                    return

                current = nxt.group(1)

asyncio.run(traverse(
    "8d13cf4dfa0921c32dbb9542c97867ee",
    "http://<instance>.cybertalentslabs.com"
))

